'''Echo Kellum''' (born August 29, 1982){{citation needed|date=July 2018}} is an American actor and comedian. Kellum is best known for his roles as [[Mister Terrific (comics)|Curtis Holt]] on [[The CW]] drama series ''[[Arrow (TV series)|Arrow]]'', Tommy on the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|FOX]] sitcom ''[[Ben and Kate]]'',<ref name="dallasnews">{{cite web |author=Robert Wilonsky |url=http://popcultureblog.dallasnews.com/2012/12/echo-kellum-co-star-of-foxs-ben-and-kate-was-in-town-promoting-his-show-this-is-our-visit.html/ |title=Echo Kellum, co-star of FOX’s ‘Ben and Kate,’ was in town promoting his show. This is our visit. |work=The Dallas Morning News Pop Culture Blog |publisher=The Dallas Morning News Inc. |date=December 4, 2012 |accessdate=2016-04-05}}</ref> and Hunter on [[NBC]]'s ''[[Sean Saves the World]]''.<ref name="NYPost">{{cite web |author=Michael Starr |url=https://nypost.com/2013/10/02/will-grace-vet-best-reason-to-watch-sean-saves-the-world/ |title=‘Will & Grace’ vet best reason to watch ‘Sean Saves the World’ |work=[[New York Post]] |date=October 2, 2013 |accessdate=2016-04-05 |quote=...and Hayes is nicely supported by Echo Kellum and Megan Hilty as co-workers Hunter (he of the understated sarcasm) and Liz (also Sean’s best friend outside the office).}}</ref>
==Early life == Born in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]],<ref>{{cite news |author=Darel Jevens |url=http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/chicagos-echo-kellum-cast-as-mr-terrific-on-arrow/ |title=Chicago’s Echo Kellum cast as Mr. Terrific on ‘Arrow’ |work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]] |date=July 20, 2015 |accessdate=2016-06-02}}</ref> he moved to Los Angeles in late 2009 to pursue a career in comedy.<ref name="UCB">{{cite web|url=http://losangeles.ucbtheatre.com/talent/view/21329 |title=UCB Theatre • Echo Kellum |publisher=UCB Comedy |date= |accessdate=2012-12-07}}</ref> He is a graduate of [[The Groundlings]], [[I.O. West]], and the [[Upright Citizens Brigade]].<ref name="dallasnews"/><ref name="UCB"/>
==Career== Kellum gained his first major role in 2012 when he was cast in the FOX comedy ''[[Ben and Kate]]'' (then titled ''Ben Fox Is My Manny'') playing the role of Tommy, the best friend of the titular character Ben ([[Nat Faxon]]).<ref>{{cite web |author=Nellie Andreeva |url=http://deadline.com/2012/02/michael-arden-joins-anger-management-echo-kellum-cast-in-ben-fox-is-my-manny-230758/ |title=Michael Arden Joins 'Anger Management', Echo Kellum Cast In 'Ben Fox Is My Manny' |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=February 14, 2012 |accessdate=2016-04-05}}</ref> Following ''Ben and Kate'', Kellum was cast as Hunter in NBC's ''[[Sean Saves the World]]'' starring [[Sean Hayes (actor)|Sean Hayes]] and [[Megan Hilty]].
In 2015, Kellum was cast in the recurring role of Curtis Holt, based on the [[DC Comics|DC]] character [[Mister Terrific (comics)|Mister Terrific]], in the fourth season of The CW drama series ''[[Arrow (TV series)|Arrow]]''.<ref name="EW-Arrow">{{cite web |author=Natalie Abrams |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/07/16/arrow-echo-kellum-mr-terrific-season-4 |title=Arrow casts Mr. Terrific for season 4 |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=July 17, 2015 |accessdate=2016-04-05}}</ref> Curtis is a technological savant and inventor who works at Palmer Technologies under the supervision of Felicity Smoak, and later becomes a member of Team Arrow. In April 2016, it was announced that Kellum would be promoted to series regular for the fifth season of ''Arrow''.<ref name="TVL-Arrow">{{cite web |author=Matt Webb Mitovich |url=http://tvline.com/2016/04/04/arrow-season-5-echo-kellum-series-regular-curtis/ |title=Arrow Season 5: Echo Kellum Promoted to Series Regular as Curtis |work=[[TVLine]] |date=April 4, 2016 |accessdate=2016-04-05}}</ref>
In 2017,<ref>http://fanfest.com/2016/07/06/echo-kellum-talks-about-the-future-of-arrows-mister-terrific</ref> Kellum appeared in [[Netflix]]'s ''[[Girlfriend's Day]]''<ref>{{cite web |author=Rebecca Ford |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/netflix-nabs-chris-sparlings-mercy-842494 |title=Netflix Nabs Chris Sparling's 'Mercy,' 'Girlfriend's Day' With Bob Odenkirk (Exclusive) |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=November 23, 2015}}</ref> as Madsen, beat poet and a co-worker of [[Bob Odenkirk]]'s character.<ref>http://www.talentmonthly.com/arrows-echo-kellum-talks-playing-curtis-mr-terrific-and-more/</ref>
Kellum voices the character "King Joaquín" on the [[Disney Channel]] animated series ''[[Elena of Avalor]]''. He also voices multiple characters for the [[Adult Swim]] animated series ''[[Rick and Morty]]''.
